Over-Smoked Scotch Ale
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> "b...@yahoo.com" &lt;brian.s...@gmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-01-23T14:03:00 </POSTDATE>
I made up a Wee Heavy Scotch Ale and wanted it to have a bit of a smoke
character, so I added 1lb of peated malt.  I tasted it after a week
when it was transfered to secondary and the smoke was a bit more than I
wanted.  I wanted a background note and it was a mild foreground
flavor.  I tried it again last night after racking to keg (2 weeks from
brew) and the smoke flavor seems stronger now than it was last week.
The beer needs a little aging time as it is, but I'm wondering what to
expect from the smoke...  Will it mellow over the next few weeks or
will it maintain its flavor?
</POST>
