I'm not sure how it will age, I'd say it'll mellow but that's just a guess.

FWIW, traditionally the smokiness comes from the yeast.  They don't
actually use peated malt in beer brewing, that stuff is for making Scotch
Whiskey.  Many homebrewers use it, but next time maybe try getting rid
of it and using a good scotch ale yeast instead.  See if that gives you
the subtle character you're after.

John.
