Last time I made a Scotch ale I added a little peated malt (1/4lb I
think) and used white labs edinburgh yeast.  It had no smoke flavor.
This time I used 1 lb and used the Wyeast Scotch ale yeast which I've
been told will add more smohe phenolic than the White Labs.  I guess
the combination of both the Smoked grain and the yeast was too much.
